headline: Accenture CEO reveals common AI mistakes she sees companies make and 3 red flags to watch out for
summary: Accenture CEO Julie Sweet sat down with Fortune Editor-in-Chief Alyson Shontell for the launch of Fortune’s new vodcast, Fortune 500: Titans and Disruptors of Industry, where she shared the three red flags companies need to watch out for in the age of AI.

headline: Accenture’s CEO manages her work-life balance by making sure she has no “regrets”
summary: Accenture CEO ⁠Julie Sweet is one of the most powerful executives in the world, overseeing a 770,000–person workforce at consulting giant Accenture. ⁠ In an interview with Fortune Editor-in-Chief Alyson Shontell for Fortune’s new vodcast Fortune 500: Titans and Disruptors of Industry, Sweet said she manages her work-life balance by making sure she has “no regrets.”
